    <subfield code="y">00002 The cosmological constant $\Lambda (t)$ obtained in the limit case $ A=0$, fixing the constants as $C_{1}=0$, $C_{2}=10^{-155}$. We highlight how, for these values of $C_{1}$, $C_{2}$, the cosmological constant at today time ($t=13.7$ billions of years, i.e. $ct\approx 1.3\times 10^{26}m$) acquires the expected value of $\Lambda _{0}=10^{-52}m^{-2}$. This value is in proximity of the minimum of the function.</subfield>
  </datafield>
